1
00:00:01,826 --> 00:00:03,850
A breakup is inevitable.

2
00:00:03,875 --> 00:00:07,003
Don't try to force it. Just don't.

3
00:00:07,028 --> 00:00:08,617
Holding on will only
bring you pain.

4
00:00:08,641 --> 00:00:10,188
Cut ties now. Get it over with.

5
00:00:10,212 --> 00:00:12,172
It's better to hurt now
and be done with it, okay?

6
00:00:47,117 --> 00:00:48,984
Can you please just go to sleep?

7
00:00:50,840 --> 00:00:52,240
You keep fidgeting.

8
00:00:52,862 --> 00:00:54,840
Is something wrong, Ohn?

9
00:00:58,200 --> 00:00:59,760
Sorry... sorry, Jee.

10
00:01:00,768 --> 00:01:01,784
Go back to sleep.

11
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:36,880
"Sheep number 1..."

12
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:40,000
"Sheep number 2..."

13
00:01:42,280 --> 00:01:43,560
"Sheep number 3..."

14
00:01:45,818 --> 00:01:47,160
"Sheep number 4..."

15
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:51,000
"Sheep number 5..."

16
00:01:53,548 --> 00:01:55,920
"Sheep number... 771."

17
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:07,920
I ran out of sheep.

18
00:02:10,680 --> 00:02:11,692
My name is Ohn.

19
00:02:12,574 --> 00:02:13,907
I'm originally from Nakhon Nayok.

20
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:17,680
But my parents split up
when I was in middle school.

21
00:02:17,705 --> 00:02:20,405
So I moved with my mom
to study here in Bangkok.

22
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:24,575
Back then, I had this one close friend.

23
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:27,575
His family ran a video rental shop.

24
00:02:27,600 --> 00:02:29,520
So we hung out at
his place all the time.

25
00:02:31,920 --> 00:02:34,078
This is a video cassette player.

26
00:02:34,103 --> 00:02:36,935
A lot of you younger kids
have probably never seen one.

27
00:02:36,960 --> 00:02:39,400
But if you're 40 or over, well...

28
00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:44,495
Even though we didn't have internet
or streaming back then,

29
00:02:44,520 --> 00:02:46,360
I still got to watch
a lot of movies.

30
00:02:49,481 --> 00:02:53,000
Back then, Brooke Shields and
Sophie Marceau were huge.

31
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,760
All the guys were crazy about them.

32
00:02:55,357 --> 00:02:57,895
Talking about how cute they were.

33
00:02:57,920 --> 00:03:02,086
So, I tried staring at their photos
all night long.

34
00:03:02,111 --> 00:03:06,200
I really wanted to like them.

35
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:10,835
But no matter how hard I looked,

36
00:03:10,860 --> 00:03:11,880
I didn't feel a thing.

37
00:03:14,613 --> 00:03:16,495
I even tried having a girlfriend.

38
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:18,983
She was a close friend of mine.

39
00:03:19,008 --> 00:03:21,920
We tried kissing,
mimicking that spaghetti scene

40
00:03:21,945 --> 00:03:24,317
from the cartoon Lady and the Tramp.

41
00:03:28,113 --> 00:03:29,113
But...

42
00:03:31,775 --> 00:03:32,920
It just felt totally icky.

43
00:03:33,880 --> 00:03:36,843
Until my friend put on a movie,

44
00:03:36,868 --> 00:03:39,240
My Own Private Idaho.

45
00:03:40,705 --> 00:03:42,537
As soon as I saw River Phoenix,

46
00:03:42,562 --> 00:03:44,643
I felt this feeling that

47
00:03:45,390 --> 00:03:46,680
I had never felt before.

48
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:50,120
So, I knew right then.

49
00:03:51,114 --> 00:03:52,538
I like men.

50
00:03:55,440 --> 00:03:57,575
Fast forward many years later.

51
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,160
I became a comic book artist.

52
00:04:00,040 --> 00:04:03,600
And at a book fair
7 years ago, I met him.

53
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:07,770
Can I get your autograph?

54
00:04:09,652 --> 00:04:11,694
- Sure.
- I really love your work.

55
00:04:11,719 --> 00:04:13,520
My name is Jira.

56
00:04:15,240 --> 00:04:16,240
Thank you.

57
00:04:25,038 --> 00:04:28,878
"Enjoy reading."

58
00:04:31,181 --> 00:04:32,181
Thank you.

59
00:04:33,024 --> 00:04:34,790
Can we take a picture together?

60
00:04:35,280 --> 00:04:36,280
Of course.

61
00:06:36,290 --> 00:06:39,320
It felt like the perfect ending
to a happy romance novel.

62
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:46,640
The Two of Cups.

63
00:06:47,480 --> 00:06:48,996
That means good love, right?

64
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:54,000
It's reversed.

65
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:57,240
See? It's upside down.

66
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,986
Wait, what does that mean?

67
00:07:01,011 --> 00:07:03,883
It means a breakup.

68
00:07:06,240 --> 00:07:08,025
No, that can't be true.

69
00:07:08,050 --> 00:07:09,560
Look, try one more card.

70
00:07:11,240 --> 00:07:12,240
Go ahead.

71
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:29,135
It's clear.

72
00:07:29,160 --> 00:07:30,160
Crystal clear.

73
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,593
You have absolutely terrible fate.

74
00:07:34,800 --> 00:07:38,484
Oh my. Besides your career
being a total flop,

75
00:07:38,509 --> 00:07:42,400
your health is just awful,

76
00:07:42,400 --> 00:07:46,495
your face is full of wrinkles,
and as for love?

77
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:47,920
A breakup.

78
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:49,920
No way.

79
00:07:50,544 --> 00:07:51,975
We still love each other.

80
00:07:52,000 --> 00:07:55,080
We've been together a long time.

81
00:07:55,105 --> 00:07:57,655
Together a long time?
How many years?

82
00:07:57,680 --> 00:08:00,600
- Coming up on seven.
- Oh god, you're doomed!

83
00:08:00,624 --> 00:08:03,414
Seven years. That's exactly
when people break up.

84
00:08:03,439 --> 00:08:04,520
Hey!

85
00:08:05,480 --> 00:08:07,157
It's the "Seven Year Itch."

86
00:08:07,182 --> 00:08:09,208
There's tons of research on this.

87
00:08:09,232 --> 00:08:11,935
Couples tend to split up
in the seventh year

88
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:14,560
because relationship
satisfaction drops.

89
00:08:15,919 --> 00:08:21,015
Correct. Impermanence.
Nothing lasts forever.

90
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:25,095
To keep a life partnership going,
there are many factors, you know?

91
00:08:25,120 --> 00:08:30,640
Family, kids, sex,
the people around you,

92
00:08:30,640 --> 00:08:32,401
or even money.

93
00:08:32,426 --> 00:08:33,426
Yes.

94
00:08:33,953 --> 00:08:35,440
- You're spot on.
- Stop it!

95
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,846
Why are you cheering her on, Chon?

96
00:08:37,640 --> 00:08:38,640
Quiet.

97
00:08:42,659 --> 00:08:43,840
Listen.

98
00:08:44,512 --> 00:08:48,088
I wasn't the one speaking just now.

99
00:08:48,088 --> 00:08:50,200
The Universe was speaking.

100
00:08:52,689 --> 00:08:56,679
Come on, let's focus.
Focus, okay?

101
00:08:56,704 --> 00:08:59,679
And listen to the voice of
the Universe. Listen.

102
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,560
- Focus.
- Yes.

103
00:09:03,560 --> 00:09:06,560
- Listen to the Universe.
- Right. Listen to the Universe.

104
00:09:07,200 --> 00:09:08,492
Listen to the Universe.

105
00:09:08,517 --> 00:09:10,164
Deep breath in, Ohn.

106
00:09:10,189 --> 00:09:11,280
Breathe out.

107
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,000
Breathe in.

108
00:09:13,880 --> 00:09:14,880
Breathe out.

109
00:09:16,950 --> 00:09:17,950
Oh god, no.

110
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,231
One more card.

111
00:09:21,960 --> 00:09:22,960
Be my guest.

112
00:09:33,080 --> 00:09:35,172
"On our 7th anniversary,"

113
00:09:35,197 --> 00:09:37,786
"what will happen to
Ohn and Jee's love?"

114
00:09:37,811 --> 00:09:40,360
"Universe, please tell me."

115
00:09:50,479 --> 00:09:51,560
Whoa...

116
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:55,226
The Universe has been screaming
until it's blue in the face.

117
00:09:55,251 --> 00:09:57,055
You still don't believe it?

118
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,320
I've got goosebumps already.

119
00:09:58,320 --> 00:10:02,155
I don't believe it. Not listening.
I don't want to know anything.

120
00:10:02,180 --> 00:10:03,895
I don't want to know anymore.

121
00:10:03,920 --> 00:10:06,215
The Universe is
literally saying "Death."

122
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:08,465
D... E... A... T... H...

123
00:10:08,490 --> 00:10:09,766
Death.

124
00:10:09,791 --> 00:10:13,895
Look, a breakup is inevitable.
Don't force it.

125
00:10:13,920 --> 00:10:18,127
Sometimes,
staying close only hurts more.

126
00:10:18,152 --> 00:10:21,520
Cut ties now. Get it over with.
Better to hurt and be done with it.

127
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:26,910
Starting over
isn't that bad, really.

128
00:10:26,935 --> 00:10:28,200
Okay, my turn!

129
00:10:28,225 --> 00:10:30,240
- I want to know about my future.
- Alright.

130
00:10:30,265 --> 00:10:31,959
- I'm moving to another country.
- Where?

131
00:10:31,984 --> 00:10:35,816
Will my visa get approved?
I'm going to Canada.

132
00:10:35,841 --> 00:10:37,000
Ah...

133
00:12:54,509 --> 00:12:55,560
Jee...

134
00:13:12,398 --> 00:13:13,418
Jee...

135
00:13:19,934 --> 00:13:22,287
Jee, how many times
have I told you?

136
00:13:22,312 --> 00:13:24,267
Turn the water heater back down
when you're done.

137
00:13:24,292 --> 00:13:26,509
It's scalding hot.
I'm practically boiled alive here.

138
00:13:26,534 --> 00:13:29,273
Oh, come on, Ohn.

139
00:13:29,298 --> 00:13:32,222
Before you turn on the shower,
just test it with your hand first.

140
00:13:32,247 --> 00:13:35,276
Just turn it back down for me.
Is that so hard?

141
00:13:38,640 --> 00:13:39,855
What are you looking for?

142
00:13:39,880 --> 00:13:41,320
My gray shirt.

143
00:13:42,135 --> 00:13:44,600
Which gray one? You have tons.

144
00:13:44,600 --> 00:13:46,232
The one I like to wear.

145
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:49,080
- Oh, your favorite one?
- Yeah.

146
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:51,240
I washed it yesterday.

147
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:56,638
Here, this one, right?

148
00:13:56,663 --> 00:13:57,935
But I haven't ironed it yet.

149
00:13:57,960 --> 00:14:00,763
Oh, never mind.
I'll just wear something else.

150
00:14:01,630 --> 00:14:03,896
No, it's okay. Just wait a sec.
I'll iron it for you.

151
00:14:03,921 --> 00:14:04,925
Okay?

152
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:13,068
I told you, we could just
use a laundry service.

153
00:14:13,093 --> 00:14:14,953
So you wouldn't have to
go to all this trouble.

154
00:14:15,680 --> 00:14:18,375
Jee, it's no trouble at all.

155
00:14:18,400 --> 00:14:20,775
I told you,
it's just the two of us.

156
00:14:20,800 --> 00:14:23,722
We don't have that many clothes.
I can handle it.

157
00:14:28,673 --> 00:14:29,673
Crap!

158
00:14:32,840 --> 00:14:34,080
I'm sorry.

159
00:14:37,360 --> 00:14:39,950
It's fine.
I'll just wear a different one.

160
00:14:43,843 --> 00:14:47,840
Ooh, my favorite dish!
Haven't had this in ages.

161
00:14:47,865 --> 00:14:51,396
Wait, isn't avocado
out of season right now?

162
00:14:52,160 --> 00:14:55,400
I bought imported ones.
Not the local ones from Chiang Mai.

163
00:14:55,909 --> 00:14:58,160
Hmm... you really went all out.

164
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,800
Well, today is a special day.

165
00:15:03,160 --> 00:15:04,160
A special day?

166
00:15:06,080 --> 00:15:07,203
Want some coffee, Jee?

167
00:15:07,733 --> 00:15:08,733
Sure.

168
00:15:17,853 --> 00:15:19,773
- Oops!
- Ow!

169
00:15:19,798 --> 00:15:20,999
- Ow! Hot!
- Jee!

170
00:15:21,024 --> 00:15:22,788
- Are you okay, Jee?
- Ow, ow...

171
00:15:22,813 --> 00:15:25,147
- Wipe it off. Are you okay?
- It's fine. Forget it.

172
00:15:25,172 --> 00:15:26,897
- I need to go change my shirt.
- I'm sorry.

173
00:15:26,922 --> 00:15:27,924
It's fine, really.

174
00:15:28,407 --> 00:15:29,480
I'll just change.

175
00:15:36,800 --> 00:15:38,095
I'm back, I'm back.

176
00:15:38,120 --> 00:15:40,080
- Come on. Eat something first.
- Ugh.

177
00:15:40,105 --> 00:15:41,520
No, I can't eat. I have to run.

178
00:15:41,545 --> 00:15:44,200
Gib just called to nag me.
I have to go meet a client on-site.

179
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:47,874
Apparently the factory messed up
the order or something.

180
00:15:47,899 --> 00:15:49,680
Wait... give me a kiss first.

181
00:15:50,563 --> 00:15:51,564
Ouch!

182
00:15:51,589 --> 00:15:52,680
Ow!

183
00:15:53,225 --> 00:15:54,232
Ow!

184
00:15:54,446 --> 00:15:55,640
Sorry!

185
00:15:57,043 --> 00:15:58,049
Ouch...

186
00:16:00,480 --> 00:16:01,480
Oh boy.

187
00:16:01,676 --> 00:16:02,976
I just wanted to...

188
00:16:04,135 --> 00:16:05,615
give you a peck before work.

189
00:16:12,203 --> 00:16:13,203
Oh...

190
00:16:14,234 --> 00:16:16,087
- Jee...
- Hmm?

191
00:16:18,861 --> 00:16:21,080
Do you think... these days...

192
00:16:22,939 --> 00:16:24,040
...how are we doing?

193
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:26,960
How? How what?

194
00:16:28,088 --> 00:16:29,145
I mean...

195
00:16:30,020 --> 00:16:33,400
These days, are you happy?

196
00:16:35,178 --> 00:16:36,661
Yeah, it's fine.

197
00:16:38,278 --> 00:16:39,518
- It's fine.
- Mmm.

198
00:16:39,543 --> 00:16:40,635
That's it?

199
00:16:40,660 --> 00:16:43,120
Yeah, that's it. Gotta go.
In a rush, bye.

200
00:16:43,145 --> 00:16:44,246
- Jee...
- Hmm.

201
00:16:45,745 --> 00:16:46,758
Agh!

202
00:16:48,503 --> 00:16:50,280
Okay. See you later.

203
00:16:50,304 --> 00:16:51,304
Bye bye, Jee.

204
00:16:51,569 --> 00:16:52,569
...Bye.

205
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:03,453
"A breakup is inevitable."

206
00:17:03,478 --> 00:17:07,436
"Sometimes,
staying close only hurts more."

207
00:17:07,461 --> 00:17:11,030
"Cut ties now. Get it over with.
Better to hurt and be done with it"

208
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:20,120
This draft isn't going to work.

209
00:17:21,246 --> 00:17:22,246
Why not?

210
00:17:22,668 --> 00:17:27,107
This whole Isekai, portal-fantasy,
time-travel trope, is played out.

211
00:17:27,132 --> 00:17:29,560
The kids are bored of it.
Nobody reads that stuff anymore.

212
00:17:30,804 --> 00:17:31,804
But my last story--

213
00:17:31,829 --> 00:17:34,535
But your last story
had terrible numbers.

214
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:36,606
We promoted the heck out of it
and it still flopped.

215
00:17:40,001 --> 00:17:42,215
I'm going to be
straight with you, Ohn.

216
00:17:42,240 --> 00:17:45,933
I need something fresh.
Something that pops. A real hit.

217
00:17:45,958 --> 00:17:47,565
Like...

218
00:17:47,589 --> 00:17:51,383
The Sorceress of the Enchanted City
that you wrote back in the day.

219
00:17:52,230 --> 00:17:53,840
But that was an Isekai story too.

220
00:17:55,960 --> 00:17:59,493
That was seven years ago.
It was fresh then.

221
00:17:59,493 --> 00:18:00,920
But it doesn't work now.

222
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:04,920
Stop clinging to the old style.

223
00:18:05,645 --> 00:18:07,525
You need to open a new door.
Find a new angle.

224
00:18:11,173 --> 00:18:12,173
Okay.

225
00:18:12,794 --> 00:18:16,400
Give me something commercial.
Just change the genre, got it?

226
00:18:18,088 --> 00:18:22,051
So, for this draft, do you want me
to go back and tweak anything?

227
00:18:22,076 --> 00:18:25,522
Don't bother tweaking.
Just start over completely.

228
00:18:25,547 --> 00:18:26,600
Okay, Ohn?

229
00:18:37,708 --> 00:18:39,480
Hello, sweetie? Liu, baby...

230
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:42,520
Aww, don't be mad at me.

231
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:46,486
I told you, I'm so busy with work.

232
00:18:46,511 --> 00:18:48,976
I've got such a headache right now.

233
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:53,640
Mmm, I want to hold you too, babe.

234
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:56,200
Okay...

235
00:18:57,800 --> 00:18:59,923
Yeah, I won't be home late.

236
00:19:04,356 --> 00:19:06,400
Yes, in time for dinner.

237
00:19:08,080 --> 00:19:09,280
Okay...

238
00:19:10,274 --> 00:19:12,000
This color is all wrong.

239
00:19:12,963 --> 00:19:15,819
You know, I ordered red. Red.

240
00:19:16,372 --> 00:19:17,640
Why did I get pink?

241
00:19:19,273 --> 00:19:22,105
How are you going to fix this?

242
00:19:22,137 --> 00:19:23,417
You know?

243
00:19:23,442 --> 00:19:27,366
I placed an order with you,

244
00:19:27,391 --> 00:19:31,096
even though I was offered
a better price from China.

245
00:19:31,941 --> 00:19:34,875
I ordered from you
because of your quality.

246
00:19:34,900 --> 00:19:36,130
But look at this!

247
00:19:36,804 --> 00:19:38,844
This is a disaster.

248
00:19:38,869 --> 00:19:41,360
Mr. Tony, I'm so sorry.

249
00:19:41,384 --> 00:19:44,420
I believe this is
a miscommunication problem.

250
00:19:44,445 --> 00:19:46,670
I'm very, very sorry Mr. Tony.

251
00:19:47,546 --> 00:19:48,978
Miscommunication?

252
00:19:49,888 --> 00:19:51,641
You were reckless.

253
00:19:53,517 --> 00:19:54,517
Uh...

254
00:19:55,317 --> 00:19:56,317
Um...

255
00:19:57,120 --> 00:19:59,664
We sincerely apologize for this.

256
00:19:59,664 --> 00:20:03,015
It was a recklessness on our part.

257
00:20:03,040 --> 00:20:06,661
We are truly sorry, Mr. Tony.

258
00:20:06,686 --> 00:20:08,480
- Right.
- So...

259
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:11,205
How are you going to fix this?

260
00:20:11,230 --> 00:20:13,437
You tell me.

261
00:20:13,462 --> 00:20:18,320
Uh... first, I'm Jira,
a Senior Marketing Manager here.

262
00:20:21,358 --> 00:20:23,303
Uh... how about this?

263
00:20:24,029 --> 00:20:25,327
What would you say, Mr. Tony?

264
00:20:25,327 --> 00:20:31,167
If we have Jeff wear this hoodie.

265
00:20:31,192 --> 00:20:34,335
And then we have him post it
on his Social Media.

266
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:37,415
Jeff has a huge following
in Singapore.

267
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:39,200
And we've worked with him before.

268
00:20:41,457 --> 00:20:43,457
But, the color.

269
00:20:43,481 --> 00:20:45,273
That's the point.

270
00:20:45,297 --> 00:20:47,726
This year, there is
a massive global campaign

271
00:20:47,750 --> 00:20:51,695
raising awareness
for breast cancer.

272
00:20:51,720 --> 00:20:54,160
And the official color
for that campaign is...

273
00:20:56,400 --> 00:20:57,400
Exactly.

274
00:20:57,830 --> 00:20:59,120
Pink.

275
00:21:01,377 --> 00:21:02,673
Breast cancer?

276
00:21:02,698 --> 00:21:04,991
- Yes, sir.
- Oh, come on.

277
00:21:05,680 --> 00:21:09,596
Cancer is a devastating disease
that affects a range of people.

278
00:21:09,621 --> 00:21:12,174
Hundreds of millions worldwide.

279
00:21:12,199 --> 00:21:15,080
And right now, whether
it's celebrities or top brands

280
00:21:15,105 --> 00:21:16,560
anyone who cares about their image

281
00:21:16,560 --> 00:21:21,283
is jumping on board to join
this campaign and raise awareness.

282
00:21:25,080 --> 00:21:27,838
Mr. Tony, did you know

283
00:21:27,863 --> 00:21:30,410
that men can get breast cancer too?

284
00:21:34,803 --> 00:21:35,804
No.

285
00:21:35,829 --> 00:21:38,964
That is exactly
why we need to speak up.

286
00:21:38,989 --> 00:21:42,222
To raise awareness.

287
00:21:42,247 --> 00:21:45,703
For every gender.
Men and women alike.

288
00:21:45,728 --> 00:21:47,728
Trans. Non-binary.

289
00:21:47,753 --> 00:21:53,040
To keep them safe and free
from breast cancer.

290
00:22:12,830 --> 00:22:14,617
Thank you so much, Mr. Tony,

291
00:22:14,641 --> 00:22:16,004
for your understanding.

292
00:22:16,028 --> 00:22:20,334
I would like to give you 15%
discount to show our appreciation.

293
00:22:20,358 --> 00:22:22,758
And sorry again for our mistake.

294
00:22:23,549 --> 00:22:26,298
Thank you very much,
but I think it's okay.

295
00:22:27,108 --> 00:22:28,715
Sometimes, it happens.

296
00:22:29,851 --> 00:22:31,111
But...

297
00:22:31,135 --> 00:22:35,557
I think I'll turn this disaster
into an opportunity.

298
00:22:37,468 --> 00:22:39,950
So, I have to say thank you
to Mr. Jira,

299
00:22:41,872 --> 00:22:43,872
for giving me this idea.

300
00:22:44,443 --> 00:22:45,652
I think I love it.

301
00:22:47,809 --> 00:22:50,455
- Thank you.
- Thank you. Thank you so much.

302
00:23:00,680 --> 00:23:03,706
Did you just break up
with your boyfriend?

303
00:23:03,731 --> 00:23:05,320
Yes.

304
00:23:05,995 --> 00:23:10,800
Ji, that bastard. He cheated on me.

305
00:23:11,376 --> 00:23:15,400
Thank god I still have my babies
to keep me company.

306
00:23:16,960 --> 00:23:18,855
How did you know?

307
00:23:18,880 --> 00:23:21,000
Just a feeling. My gut told me.

308
00:23:21,599 --> 00:23:22,637
- Ouch!
- What is it?

309
00:23:23,400 --> 00:23:24,400
Does it hurt?

310
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:27,720
I feel like I'm dying.

311
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:30,175
Oh, sorry, sorry! Let me get you
some numbing cream.

312
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:31,822
- No.
- Huh?

313
00:23:31,847 --> 00:23:33,440
It's my heart that hurts.

314
00:23:34,559 --> 00:23:38,320
Your tattooing doesn't hurt at all.
You have such a light touch.

315
00:23:40,607 --> 00:23:42,640
Do you have a boyfriend?

316
00:23:42,665 --> 00:23:43,680
I do.

317
00:23:43,680 --> 00:23:47,200
He must be really handsome.

318
00:23:51,049 --> 00:23:52,640
You be careful, okay?

319
00:23:53,338 --> 00:23:57,095
Men can't be trusted.

320
00:23:57,120 --> 00:23:59,161
They're all players.

321
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:07,056
I think I'm gonna become a lesbian.
Dating women has got to be better.

322
00:24:09,082 --> 00:24:10,142
Here.

323
00:24:12,112 --> 00:24:14,552
Let's take a break
to cry for a sec, okay?

324
00:24:14,585 --> 00:24:15,996
Then we can start again.

325
00:24:22,772 --> 00:24:23,778
What's up?

326
00:24:23,803 --> 00:24:26,120
That fortune teller
was scary accurate.

327
00:24:26,144 --> 00:24:27,144
Yeah?

328
00:24:27,670 --> 00:24:29,502
Did you break up with Jee already?

329
00:24:29,527 --> 00:24:32,320
Watch your mouth! ...Not yet!

330
00:24:33,288 --> 00:24:38,615
But work is a total disaster.
Everything got rejected.

331
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:41,263
My editor was absolutely brutal.

332
00:24:41,288 --> 00:24:43,716
Seriously, I'm about to cry here.

333
00:24:44,560 --> 00:24:48,746
Does this mean I'm really
going to break up with Jee?

334
00:24:48,771 --> 00:24:52,108
This 7-Year Itch,
is it actually real, Chon?

335
00:24:52,133 --> 00:24:55,757
Ohn, did you seriously call me
just to ask that?

336
00:24:55,782 --> 00:24:58,688
Relationships are about effort.

337
00:24:58,713 --> 00:25:01,059
Both sides have to
put in the work, don't they?

338
00:25:01,084 --> 00:25:02,647
And if you do break up,

339
00:25:02,671 --> 00:25:05,400
it means one side stopped trying.

340
00:25:05,400 --> 00:25:08,790
What curse?
You are so superstitious.

341
00:25:08,815 --> 00:25:10,082
Oh...

342
00:25:10,106 --> 00:25:12,243
and you aren't superstitious
at all, right?

343
00:25:12,268 --> 00:25:15,999
I don't believe in fate.
I believe we make our own destiny.

344
00:25:16,024 --> 00:25:19,680
Right. Then why did you follow me
to the fortune teller

345
00:25:19,704 --> 00:25:21,610
and ask even more
detailed questions than I did?

346
00:25:22,525 --> 00:25:25,321
I... I... I'm busy. Talk later.

347
00:25:25,346 --> 00:25:26,775
Using work as an excuse again.

348
00:25:26,800 --> 00:25:30,234
I really am with a client.
I gotta go. Talk later.

349
00:25:30,259 --> 00:25:31,259
Fine.

350
00:25:33,537 --> 00:25:34,827
- Hey, excuse me.
- Yes?

351
00:25:34,827 --> 00:25:37,240
Tell Editor Mindy I'm heading out.

352
00:25:37,265 --> 00:25:38,305
Okay, Ohn.

353
00:25:43,920 --> 00:25:44,920
Here you go.

354
00:25:46,505 --> 00:25:47,505
Is this alright?

355
00:25:48,158 --> 00:25:49,158
Yes.

356
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:53,049
Your girlfriend is
a very lucky woman.

357
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:58,880
Usually, men don't pay
much attention to birthdays,

358
00:25:58,880 --> 00:25:59,920
or anniversaries.

359
00:26:00,724 --> 00:26:02,480
...Right.

360
00:26:03,234 --> 00:26:06,038
Uh, please wrap it up for me.

361
00:26:06,063 --> 00:26:07,510
Certainly. Just a moment.

362
00:26:29,541 --> 00:26:30,621
Ouch!

363
00:26:30,646 --> 00:26:32,440
Ow! Ow!

364
00:26:33,557 --> 00:26:35,440
Why are you riding on the sidewalk?

365
00:26:36,600 --> 00:26:38,335
It's the "Seven Year Itch."

366
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:40,050
There's tons of research on this.

367
00:26:40,074 --> 00:26:42,752
Couples tend to split up
in the seventh year.

368
00:27:23,771 --> 00:27:24,840
Thank you.

369
00:27:32,341 --> 00:27:35,003
Old books here!
Cheap clearance sale!

370
00:27:35,028 --> 00:27:37,168
You can even use them
to level a wobbly table.

371
00:27:37,193 --> 00:27:38,894
Feel free to browse, uncle.

372
00:28:08,760 --> 00:28:10,375
This one is pretty good.

373
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:12,880
Even if the plot
is a little old-fashioned.

374
00:28:36,447 --> 00:28:40,008
"School Restroom"

375
00:28:40,033 --> 00:28:41,968
"Don't you think
Kit is kind of weird?"

376
00:28:41,993 --> 00:28:44,736
"Yeah, totally.
Let's just stay away from him."

377
00:28:52,846 --> 00:28:54,139
"On the way home"

378
00:29:02,465 --> 00:29:04,440
"What is something like this
doing in the forest?"

379
00:29:19,903 --> 00:29:22,870
Queen! Where did these
Cup C boobs come from?

380
00:29:29,547 --> 00:29:34,095
You! Are you a sorceress?
Tell me who you are right now!

381
00:29:34,120 --> 00:29:36,800
Are you a servant
of the Wicked Witch?

382
00:29:36,800 --> 00:29:39,221
What sorceress?
What wicked witch?

383
00:29:39,246 --> 00:29:40,800
You almost killed me!

384
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:44,275
Is this how people in this town
say hello? You barbarian!

385
00:29:44,300 --> 00:29:47,140
Forgive me.
I am Reef, Son of Gaia.

386
00:29:47,165 --> 00:29:49,040
Guardian of this Himmapan Forest.

387
00:29:50,650 --> 00:29:54,255
Wait, wait. There are Elves
in the Himmapan Forest?

388
00:29:54,280 --> 00:29:57,281
That's crazy. I thought they were
only in Mirkwood.

389
00:29:57,281 --> 00:30:00,535
What about you? Are you
a Makkali-pon fruit maiden?

390
00:30:00,560 --> 00:30:03,295
Why have I never seen
your kind before?

391
00:30:03,320 --> 00:30:05,440
What kind of creature are you?

392
00:30:06,433 --> 00:30:08,019
I am...

393
00:30:08,043 --> 00:30:10,546
I guess I'm a woman now.

394
00:30:10,571 --> 00:30:11,691
And your name?

395
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:15,480
My name is Kit... er, Kittima.

396
00:30:16,080 --> 00:30:18,855
And this is my companion, Duckman.

397
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,040
Come on out, Duckman.

398
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:25,320
Hello there, Duckman.

399
00:30:25,345 --> 00:30:28,253
Wait, you mentioned
a Wicked Witch earlier, Reef?

400
00:30:28,278 --> 00:30:30,655
The evil witch Laila.

401
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:35,781
The people have suffered
under her power for far too long.

402
00:30:35,806 --> 00:30:37,000
Isn't that right, Duckman?

403
00:30:39,665 --> 00:30:41,240
Oh! What is that thing?

404
00:30:41,987 --> 00:30:44,016
A Griffin-Beast.

405
00:30:50,909 --> 00:30:52,801
Now, Reef! Hurry!

406
00:30:57,317 --> 00:30:59,596
Don't you have any skills at all?

407
00:30:59,621 --> 00:31:00,510
Nope.

408
00:31:00,535 --> 00:31:02,773
Then why did you tag along?

409
00:31:02,798 --> 00:31:04,120
Just go be roast duck already.

410
00:31:04,120 --> 00:31:07,161
If you're going to be useless,
at least provide some nutrition.

411
00:31:07,186 --> 00:31:10,520
Come back and let me grill you.

412
00:31:13,186 --> 00:31:14,960
Thank you, Sorceress Kittima,

413
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:16,560
Lord Reef, and Duckman.

414
00:31:16,560 --> 00:31:19,400
For protecting our village
from the Griffin-Beast.

415
00:31:19,424 --> 00:31:21,256
Yay!

416
00:31:21,280 --> 00:31:24,800
"The boy named Kit
disappeared forever."

417
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:28,023
"Leaving behind only a pair of
shoes abandoned in the forest."

418
00:31:28,048 --> 00:31:31,680
"Kittima chose to stay in
the Enchanted City as a sorceress"

419
00:31:31,680 --> 00:31:33,080
"and never returned again."

420
00:31:35,560 --> 00:31:38,120
You buying it, Uncle?
Selling it cheap, 40 baht.

421
00:32:05,674 --> 00:32:07,760
Where did I put my glasses?

422
00:32:41,800 --> 00:32:48,869
"Rainy days...
usually bring the unexpected."

423
00:32:51,098 --> 00:32:52,098
Wow.

424
00:32:53,363 --> 00:32:54,363
Kids these days.

425
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:56,400
So talented.

426
00:32:59,969 --> 00:33:06,129
"So good. Reminds me
of Ohn's in the past."

427
00:33:09,659 --> 00:33:13,686
"In the beginning, right?
Not the later ones. Hahaha..."

428
00:33:13,710 --> 00:33:16,683
"How could you compare them?
Crazy!"

429
00:33:16,707 --> 00:33:20,127
"Was that a compliment?"

430
00:33:20,152 --> 00:33:21,893
"Is he still drawing?"

431
00:33:21,917 --> 00:33:26,657
"Beam is so much better."

432
00:33:36,480 --> 00:33:37,480
Ugh...

433
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:43,520
- Jee...
- Hmm?

434
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:47,440
How was your day?

435
00:33:48,960 --> 00:33:50,604
Well... nothing special.

436
00:33:53,760 --> 00:33:54,760
What?

437
00:34:05,487 --> 00:34:07,497
"Mr. Tony: I'll be in Bangkok
for a few more days."

438
00:34:07,522 --> 00:34:10,548
"Mr. Tony:
Want to have dinner together?"

439
00:34:10,573 --> 00:34:13,333
"So, I have to say thank you
to Mr. Jira,"

440
00:34:14,836 --> 00:34:17,139
"for giving me this idea."

441
00:34:17,163 --> 00:34:19,163
"I think I love it."

442
00:34:35,940 --> 00:34:38,761
Huh? You haven't prepared dinner?

443
00:34:40,830 --> 00:34:44,535
Um, I already ordered.

444
00:34:44,560 --> 00:34:46,775
Should be here in 20 minutes.

445
00:34:46,800 --> 00:34:49,433
What did you order?

446
00:34:49,458 --> 00:34:51,972
I told you, shop food...

447
00:34:51,997 --> 00:34:55,309
It's too salty, high in fat.
It's totally unhealthy.

448
00:34:55,309 --> 00:34:56,449
Hey!

449
00:34:56,474 --> 00:34:58,880
Why don't you make it yourself?
Since you're so picky.

450
00:34:59,680 --> 00:35:00,686
What...

451
00:35:00,711 --> 00:35:03,506
Jee, what's the matter with you?

452
00:35:03,531 --> 00:35:05,840
You walked in the door
and started complaining.

453
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:07,160
I can't do it all, you know.

454
00:35:09,322 --> 00:35:12,221
- Here. Look at this!
- God...

455
00:35:12,245 --> 00:35:15,583
A motorcycle grazed me.
My arm hurts. Did you even know?

456
00:35:15,608 --> 00:35:18,074
Well, you didn't tell me.
How am I supposed to know?

457
00:35:18,709 --> 00:35:19,879
- Fine.
- What?

458
00:35:19,904 --> 00:35:21,006
How would you know?

459
00:35:21,498 --> 00:35:24,280
Do you ever pay attention
to anything these days?

460
00:35:25,435 --> 00:35:26,435
Ah...

461
00:35:26,460 --> 00:35:27,460
Lately...

462
00:35:28,366 --> 00:35:31,720
You don't care about me
like you used to.

463
00:35:32,491 --> 00:35:34,760
You don't care about my day,

464
00:35:34,784 --> 00:35:37,040
what I've been through,
or how I am.

465
00:35:37,640 --> 00:35:39,440
Oh come on, I'm just tired!

466
00:35:39,440 --> 00:35:42,743
Work is crazy busy.
I come home and I'm drained.

467
00:35:42,768 --> 00:35:43,768
I'm tired too!

468
00:35:47,870 --> 00:35:48,870
Jee...

469
00:35:49,691 --> 00:35:50,880
A relationship...

470
00:35:51,880 --> 00:35:55,335
It takes effort from two people.

471
00:35:55,360 --> 00:35:59,880
But right now, I feel like
I'm the only one trying.

472
00:36:03,508 --> 00:36:04,560
And another thing.

473
00:36:06,026 --> 00:36:07,960
We haven't had sex in ages.

474
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:10,000
You want to do it?

475
00:36:14,503 --> 00:36:16,080
Well, you don't want to.

476
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:18,588
Every time I initiate,
I get rejected.

477
00:36:19,240 --> 00:36:20,615
Don't try to start a fight.

478
00:36:20,640 --> 00:36:23,163
So is it about that?

479
00:36:23,188 --> 00:36:24,850
So you're bored of me.

480
00:36:24,875 --> 00:36:26,815
You want to
break up with me, don't you?

481
00:36:26,840 --> 00:36:28,640
Where are you
getting this from now?

482
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:32,280
Someone told me, okay?

483
00:36:35,201 --> 00:36:37,775
You went to see
a fortune teller again, didn't you?

484
00:36:37,800 --> 00:36:38,926
The fortune teller told you?

485
00:36:40,320 --> 00:36:41,592
The Universe told me.

486
00:36:41,617 --> 00:36:42,623
Oh boy.

487
00:36:42,648 --> 00:36:45,440
Well, you go tell that Universe
to stop talking nonsense.

488
00:36:45,465 --> 00:36:47,895
Universe, multiverse,
whatever it is.

489
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:50,163
Tell it we are staying together.
Just like this.

490
00:36:51,193 --> 00:36:55,750
Even if you are whiny, grumpy,
gray-haired, or getting a belly,

491
00:36:56,887 --> 00:36:58,823
I am not going anywhere.

492
00:37:03,298 --> 00:37:04,298
Old man...

493
00:37:05,321 --> 00:37:08,116
But you really have changed.
You aren't the same.

494
00:37:16,119 --> 00:37:17,456
You changed too, Ohn.

495
00:37:19,846 --> 00:37:21,010
We grew up.

496
00:37:21,720 --> 00:37:23,703
Our relationship grew up.

497
00:37:24,055 --> 00:37:27,786
Nothing can stay the same forever.
Things have to change.

498
00:37:27,811 --> 00:37:29,876
But that doesn't mean...

499
00:37:30,839 --> 00:37:32,316
...that we don't love each other.

500
00:37:36,495 --> 00:37:37,495
Really?

501
00:37:38,584 --> 00:37:42,400
Really. I was actually planning
to book a table at a rooftop bar.

502
00:37:42,400 --> 00:37:45,323
But it's Saturday. It's chaotic,
crowds everywhere, bad traffic.

503
00:37:45,348 --> 00:37:48,850
So I rushed back and we could
be quiet together, the two of us.

504
00:37:50,382 --> 00:37:52,342
But I did make a reservation
for tomorrow instead.

505
00:37:56,600 --> 00:37:57,600
Jee...

506
00:37:58,640 --> 00:38:00,963
Did you really remember
what day it is?

507
00:38:17,351 --> 00:38:18,400
- Ow.
- Are you hurt?

508
00:38:18,773 --> 00:38:19,800
- Mmm.
- Oh.

509
00:38:20,166 --> 00:38:21,681
There, there… all better.

510
00:38:23,617 --> 00:38:25,160
Pain, pain, go away...

511
00:38:26,352 --> 00:38:29,712
Easy does it. Watch your step.
You know your knees aren't great.

512
00:38:29,745 --> 00:38:31,360
I'm fine, really. It's nothing.

513
00:38:32,760 --> 00:38:33,760
Oh, here.

514
00:38:34,666 --> 00:38:35,666
Thank you.

515
00:38:35,691 --> 00:38:36,691
After you.

516
00:38:46,943 --> 00:38:48,160
Order for Mr. Ohn.

517
00:38:49,794 --> 00:38:50,794
Ah.

518
00:38:51,079 --> 00:38:52,600
Okay. All set.

519
00:38:52,625 --> 00:38:53,869
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

520
00:38:55,323 --> 00:38:56,323
Okay.

521
00:38:59,243 --> 00:39:00,243
After you.

522
00:39:04,360 --> 00:39:05,840
Hold the door, please!

523
00:39:07,798 --> 00:39:09,352
Uh... Hey!

524
00:39:10,044 --> 00:39:11,044
What?

525
00:39:20,261 --> 00:39:21,261
Hmm.

526
00:39:24,391 --> 00:39:27,960
Why did you close it so fast?
Why didn't you wait for him?

527
00:39:27,960 --> 00:39:30,044
He stays on the floor near us.

528
00:39:30,069 --> 00:39:32,440
Eh, that guy is gay.
Didn't you know?

529
00:39:34,629 --> 00:39:38,299
Oh, honestly.
What year do you think this is?

530
00:39:38,324 --> 00:39:39,880
Still with the homophobia?

531
00:39:39,880 --> 00:39:42,640
People have a hundred different
Gender Identities these days.

532
00:39:43,736 --> 00:39:45,322
Don't give me that
"Gender" nonsense.

533
00:39:45,322 --> 00:39:47,187
That's just too much imagination.

534
00:39:47,212 --> 00:39:51,458
Biologically, humans are just
male and female, right?

535
00:39:52,240 --> 00:39:53,240
Wrong.

536
00:39:53,562 --> 00:39:58,215
If you look at human chromosomes,
there are at least 6 sexes.

537
00:39:58,240 --> 00:39:59,905
There is X...

538
00:39:59,930 --> 00:40:02,015
XX... XXY...

539
00:40:02,040 --> 00:40:04,175
XY... XYY...

540
00:40:04,200 --> 00:40:06,040
and XXXY.

541
00:40:10,760 --> 00:40:14,920
What if our son suddenly came to us
and told us he was gay?

542
00:40:14,920 --> 00:40:18,372
Would you not accept him?
Slam the door in his face?

543
00:40:18,397 --> 00:40:20,816
Would you disown him?
Cut ties with him?

544
00:40:22,080 --> 00:40:25,378
Well, if that actually happened,

545
00:40:25,403 --> 00:40:28,176
I suppose I would have to
find a way to accept it.

546
00:40:28,880 --> 00:40:31,436
But I couldn't help but worry.

547
00:40:32,120 --> 00:40:35,669
I'd worry that he wouldn't have
a happy love life.

548
00:40:36,200 --> 00:40:39,132
I'd be afraid if he would ever
find a partner.

549
00:40:39,157 --> 00:40:42,615
Would he have someone by his side
when he's old and gray?

550
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:44,295
Look at you and me.

551
00:40:44,320 --> 00:40:47,696
If we didn't have kids,
you'd probably have left me by now.

552
00:40:48,420 --> 00:40:49,520
That's true.

553
00:40:50,067 --> 00:40:54,215
But you know, every couple is
different, aren't they?

554
00:40:54,240 --> 00:40:56,888
Not everyone is the same.

555
00:40:56,913 --> 00:41:01,766
Some couples, splitting up might
actually be better for the kids.

556
00:41:01,791 --> 00:41:04,019
Just because a couple is straight,

557
00:41:04,044 --> 00:41:06,655
it doesn't guarantee
they'd find true love.

558
00:41:06,680 --> 00:41:07,863
Isn't that right?

559
00:41:11,680 --> 00:41:12,680
Oof.

560
00:41:14,080 --> 00:41:15,200
Ouch.

561
00:41:16,760 --> 00:41:17,760
Ugh.

562
00:41:19,760 --> 00:41:20,880
Oh boy.

563
00:41:29,640 --> 00:41:30,640
Oof.

564
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:34,000
Ouch.

565
00:41:37,546 --> 00:41:40,596
I can't do these stairs anymore.

566
00:41:43,240 --> 00:41:44,240
Oh.

567
00:41:44,560 --> 00:41:45,560
Here.

568
00:41:46,680 --> 00:41:48,120
I guess I'm getting old.

569
00:41:49,400 --> 00:41:51,136
You're guessing?

570
00:41:54,160 --> 00:41:56,160
I heard you're only
one year older than me.

571
00:41:58,680 --> 00:42:00,480
Let's eat. I'm starving.

572
00:42:02,171 --> 00:42:03,760
Sit, sit.

573
00:42:04,227 --> 00:42:05,227
Come on.

574
00:42:05,683 --> 00:42:06,743
Whoa, dizzy.

575
00:42:08,817 --> 00:42:10,956
Go ahead, open it up.

576
00:42:31,800 --> 00:42:34,975
It's all mushed together.
What a waste.

577
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:36,000
Mmm.

578
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:38,463
And I ordered from
your favorite place, too.

579
00:42:39,925 --> 00:42:41,243
I'm sorry, Jee.

580
00:42:42,600 --> 00:42:43,720
It's fine.

581
00:42:45,926 --> 00:42:47,436
So is your arm feeling better?

582
00:42:49,003 --> 00:42:50,003
Yeah, it's better.

583
00:42:55,040 --> 00:42:56,120
Quite a mess.

584
00:43:01,080 --> 00:43:02,426
- Is it still good?
- Mmm.

585
00:43:02,965 --> 00:43:04,098
Still delicious.

586
00:43:04,122 --> 00:43:05,256
Here.

587
00:43:05,280 --> 00:43:07,270
Let me get you some.

588
00:43:14,970 --> 00:43:15,970
Mmm.

589
00:43:18,150 --> 00:43:19,150
Okay.

590
00:43:20,480 --> 00:43:21,783
The color is beautiful.

591
00:43:23,160 --> 00:43:24,160
Mmm...

592
00:43:26,523 --> 00:43:27,787
Mmm...

593
00:43:27,812 --> 00:43:29,240
Mmm.

594
00:43:29,265 --> 00:43:30,575
Mmm.

595
00:43:30,600 --> 00:43:33,560
Even if it's messy,
it's still yummy.

596
00:43:36,055 --> 00:43:38,680
Come on, eat with me.
So pretty.

597
00:43:38,680 --> 00:43:40,870
They gave a lot of fruit.
Just like always.

598
00:43:42,937 --> 00:43:43,937
Ahh...

599
00:43:44,841 --> 00:43:46,200
- Mmm.
- Mmm.

600
00:43:46,692 --> 00:43:48,035
Mmm, good.

601
00:43:48,060 --> 00:43:49,060
- Mmm.
- Good?

602
00:43:49,708 --> 00:43:51,200
Very good.

603
00:44:14,640 --> 00:44:15,640
It'll dry soon.

604
00:44:16,515 --> 00:44:17,600
- Jee.
- Hmm?

605
00:44:17,913 --> 00:44:20,520
Do you want French Nails?

606
00:44:21,640 --> 00:44:22,640
What's that?

607
00:44:23,280 --> 00:44:27,095
It's when you paint the tips white.

608
00:44:27,120 --> 00:44:31,243
You add another layer.
It looks elegant and expensive.

609
00:44:31,268 --> 00:44:34,480
No thanks.
I want a French Kiss instead.

610
00:44:37,040 --> 00:44:38,840
That is not a French Kiss.

611
00:44:41,440 --> 00:44:43,080
Maybe I'll add some crystals then.

612
00:44:45,458 --> 00:44:47,138
No, this is enough.

613
00:44:48,047 --> 00:44:49,087
Oh boy.

614
00:44:49,419 --> 00:44:51,320
Fine. Just that then.

615
00:44:51,708 --> 00:44:55,511
Ohn, can you grab the book
in my bag for me?

616
00:44:55,545 --> 00:44:56,560
My nails aren't dry yet.

617
00:44:58,120 --> 00:44:59,360
What book?

618
00:45:05,588 --> 00:45:07,320
Oh, Kittima.

619
00:45:09,200 --> 00:45:12,315
Jee, you already have this book.
Why did you buy another one?

620
00:45:12,340 --> 00:45:15,812
Hey, this is the First Edition.

621
00:45:16,297 --> 00:45:18,616
It's exactly the same inside.

622
00:45:19,211 --> 00:45:20,360
But I want to keep it.

623
00:45:24,806 --> 00:45:26,781
Can you sign it for me?

624
00:45:26,806 --> 00:45:28,703
Just like the first time we met.

625
00:45:30,765 --> 00:45:32,160
Like at the book fair?

626
00:45:32,160 --> 00:45:33,160
Mmm.

627
00:45:37,207 --> 00:45:39,000
- Jee.
- Hmm?

628
00:45:39,024 --> 00:45:40,430
I'm asking you seriously.

629
00:45:43,960 --> 00:45:46,376
Did you like me
because of this book?

630
00:45:49,160 --> 00:45:50,440
What if I...

631
00:45:52,360 --> 00:45:54,763
What if I never produce
another hit again?

632
00:45:56,520 --> 00:45:57,640
What if my success...

633
00:45:58,967 --> 00:46:00,996
...is just from the old stuff?

634
00:46:02,019 --> 00:46:03,360
Would you still like me then?

635
00:46:07,496 --> 00:46:09,920
To be honest, I didn't actually
like your comic that much.

636
00:46:09,920 --> 00:46:11,648
At first, I bought it
for my nephew.

637
00:46:11,673 --> 00:46:13,200
Okay, thanks. Real touching.

638
00:46:14,290 --> 00:46:18,104
But I came to like it later
because you wrote it.

639
00:46:23,447 --> 00:46:27,640
Ohn, if you're stressed about work,
why didn't you tell me?

640
00:46:28,480 --> 00:46:30,200
You can complain to me, you know.

641
00:46:31,400 --> 00:46:32,400
Well...

642
00:46:33,080 --> 00:46:37,400
I was afraid you'd call me
a grumpy old man.

643
00:46:38,160 --> 00:46:40,080
I'd be happier if you just told me.

644
00:46:42,082 --> 00:46:44,512
Promise me?
If something's wrong, we talk.

645
00:46:45,582 --> 00:46:48,065
Communicate more.

646
00:46:48,090 --> 00:46:50,130
So you won't accuse me
of not trying.

647
00:46:52,432 --> 00:46:53,432
Mmm.

648
00:46:54,830 --> 00:46:55,837
Okay?

649
00:46:57,593 --> 00:46:58,593
Hey.

650
00:47:00,093 --> 00:47:01,635
Can I get that autograph now?

651
00:47:01,660 --> 00:47:02,660
Right.

652
00:47:16,314 --> 00:47:19,655
"Happy Anniversary..."

653
00:47:19,680 --> 00:47:20,680
Oh, Jee.

654
00:47:21,172 --> 00:47:24,440
- Hmm?
- Chon is moving to Canada.

655
00:47:24,440 --> 00:47:26,720
Oh, really?
Is she going with her girlfriend?

656
00:47:27,320 --> 00:47:28,320
Mmm.

657
00:47:29,406 --> 00:47:32,356
Nidnoi passed her test.
She got an offer.

658
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:34,000
Wow.

659
00:47:34,964 --> 00:47:39,440
As a nurse there, she'll make
almost 3 million a year.

660
00:47:39,465 --> 00:47:41,360
- Really?
- Mmm.

661
00:47:41,597 --> 00:47:43,108
And Chon is a tattoo artist.

662
00:47:43,133 --> 00:47:45,826
That's good. They'll probably make
a lot more money there than here.

663
00:47:47,000 --> 00:47:50,243
Good for them. They have no ties
holding them back.

664
00:47:51,160 --> 00:47:52,960
Without us,

665
00:47:53,400 --> 00:47:56,954
those two would probably
be living by themselves.

666
00:47:56,979 --> 00:48:00,363
Come to think of it, they're lucky.

667
00:48:00,933 --> 00:48:02,950
Lucky that they found each other.

668
00:48:04,800 --> 00:48:07,120
What about us?
Have we found each other yet?

669
00:48:10,480 --> 00:48:11,600
We have.

670
00:48:14,120 --> 00:48:16,840
So, what did you write?
Read it to me.

671
00:48:17,513 --> 00:48:18,880
Here.

672
00:48:19,560 --> 00:48:23,040
"Happy Anniversary, Jee."

673
00:48:24,360 --> 00:48:27,736
"Let's keep trying together.
From Ohn."

674
00:48:28,338 --> 00:48:29,338
Oh wow.

675
00:48:30,600 --> 00:48:33,031
Do you want glasses
so you can see?

676
00:48:33,056 --> 00:48:35,356
If you have to be that far away,
how about this?

677
00:48:35,381 --> 00:48:37,309
Okay, I'll be closer.
You already read it for me!

678
00:48:37,334 --> 00:48:38,349
Go ahead.

679
00:48:40,040 --> 00:48:41,240
- I can't see either!
- Hey!

680
00:48:46,643 --> 00:48:48,643
"Mr. Tony: I'll be in Bangkok
for a few more days."

681
00:48:48,668 --> 00:48:49,909
"Want to have dinner together?"

682
00:48:49,934 --> 00:48:52,657
"Jira: Thanks for the invitation,
but I'm pretty busy these days."

683
00:48:52,682 --> 00:48:55,417
"I won't miss it next time."

684
00:49:08,040 --> 00:49:10,855
"Tonight,
I'll probably sleep soundly."

685
00:49:10,880 --> 00:49:13,380
"Because at least I didn't break up
on our anniversary"

686
00:49:13,404 --> 00:49:14,813
"like the prediction."

687
00:49:15,709 --> 00:49:18,195
"Maybe I've beaten fate."

688
00:49:18,709 --> 00:49:21,676
"Maybe everything will be okay."

689
00:49:29,640 --> 00:49:31,560
- Jee...
- Hmm?

690
00:49:31,560 --> 00:49:33,116
What are you doing?

691
00:49:34,400 --> 00:49:35,736
Plucking your gray hairs.

692
00:49:36,240 --> 00:49:39,676
I was just drifting off.

693
00:49:44,491 --> 00:49:46,774
"Tonight,
I probably won't sleep at all."

694
00:49:46,799 --> 00:49:48,703
"Because of his snoring."

695
00:50:04,360 --> 00:50:05,440
Thank you.

696
00:50:08,936 --> 00:50:11,936
"7 years ago"

697
00:50:14,160 --> 00:50:15,640
Is that the one
Chon tattooed for you?

698
00:50:17,280 --> 00:50:18,680
- Yeah, that's it.
- Mmm.

699
00:50:19,737 --> 00:50:21,480
Why did you choose this image?

700
00:50:22,133 --> 00:50:25,265
Hmm... I guess because...

701
00:50:25,290 --> 00:50:28,234
I relate to this guy the most.

702
00:50:28,259 --> 00:50:29,351
Hmm?

703
00:50:29,376 --> 00:50:30,880
He's a loser.

704
00:50:31,525 --> 00:50:32,525
Useless.

705
00:50:33,277 --> 00:50:34,400
Totally pathetic.

706
00:50:35,800 --> 00:50:38,080
But a lot of people like Duckman.

707
00:50:39,478 --> 00:50:42,240
Maybe because he's funny.

708
00:50:44,645 --> 00:50:48,415
But I think most people are scared.

709
00:50:48,440 --> 00:50:52,320
And deep down inside,
they feel like they suck too.

710
00:50:53,680 --> 00:50:57,301
But someone who dares
to admit that openly?

711
00:50:57,326 --> 00:51:01,310
That, I think is
the bravest one of all.

712
00:51:04,704 --> 00:51:05,704
Not true.

713
00:51:08,368 --> 00:51:10,009
"And Ohn probably
doesn't realize it."

714
00:51:10,938 --> 00:51:13,783
"That his honesty and his stories"

715
00:51:13,808 --> 00:51:16,243
"give courage to people."

716
00:51:20,680 --> 00:51:21,806
What are you thinking about?

717
00:51:22,529 --> 00:51:23,529
Hmm?

718
00:51:24,160 --> 00:51:25,160
What's on your mind?

719
00:51:26,332 --> 00:51:30,615
"I don't know what inspired me,
but in that moment"

720
00:51:30,640 --> 00:51:35,210
"I was certain that
this was the one."

721
00:51:52,400 --> 00:51:53,400
Ohn.

722
00:51:58,080 --> 00:51:59,400
Will you move in with me?

723
00:52:09,720 --> 00:52:10,720
Yes.

724
00:52:11,480 --> 00:52:12,480
I will.

725
00:52:30,440 --> 00:52:31,520
What is it now?

726
00:52:32,224 --> 00:52:33,895
Don't start the drama right now.

727
00:52:33,920 --> 00:52:36,815
You can't distract me right now.

728
00:52:36,840 --> 00:52:40,415
Being 54 isn't exactly
a walk in the park, man.

729
00:52:40,440 --> 00:52:41,640
Don't you think?

730
00:52:42,440 --> 00:52:44,720
The new target group
we want to capture,

731
00:52:45,760 --> 00:52:47,256
nobody knows
who Kittima is anymore.

732
00:52:47,880 --> 00:52:50,480
Kittima is history.

733
00:52:52,240 --> 00:52:53,575
They act like...

734
00:52:53,600 --> 00:52:55,726
I wasn't even born
in the same era as them.

735
00:52:56,360 --> 00:52:59,659
Maybe they just don't feel safe.

736
00:52:59,684 --> 00:53:02,911
They aren't sure
if we are really on their side.

737
00:53:03,680 --> 00:53:05,175
I'm so jealous.

738
00:53:05,199 --> 00:53:07,919
I wish I had
this kind of freedom every day.

739
00:53:09,938 --> 00:53:11,280
I choose not to have a boyfriend.

740
00:53:12,040 --> 00:53:13,280
I choose to be alone.

741
00:53:14,520 --> 00:53:16,163
I don't want any attachments.

742
00:53:16,520 --> 00:53:18,196
And what about Ohn?
What did he say?

743
00:53:20,000 --> 00:53:24,320
and I hope Singapore
will be a new home for you.

744
00:53:30,151 --> 00:53:34,960
♪ Can you feel
that love still remains? ♪

745
00:53:34,960 --> 00:53:41,080
♪ Can you feel
the stories we made? ♪

746
00:53:41,080 --> 00:53:46,327
♪ No matter what stood in our way ♪

747
00:53:46,351 --> 00:53:50,019
♪ Come rain or shine ♪

748
00:53:50,044 --> 00:53:55,160
♪ Can you feel
the love from the start? ♪

749
00:53:55,160 --> 00:54:01,480
♪ Can you feel
the beat of my heart? ♪

750
00:54:01,480 --> 00:54:07,000
♪ Calling out so we never part ♪

751
00:54:07,000 --> 00:54:11,918
♪ Every day together
just you and I ♪

752
00:54:11,943 --> 00:54:16,109
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

753
00:54:16,670 --> 00:54:21,640
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

754
00:54:21,820 --> 00:54:26,680
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

755
00:54:26,896 --> 00:54:31,480
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

756
00:54:31,787 --> 00:54:36,800
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

757
00:54:36,980 --> 00:54:41,880
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

758
00:54:42,021 --> 00:54:46,960
♪ La la la la la la la ♪

759
